John, SW, I offer my apology. I read your above posts and realized I was flip and stupid with the post I last did. The stories about SAR made my heart leap, and my brain shudder, and I really sorry to insult you guys, esp. those who went in to get others.  I was wrong, way off base, and I am sorry and my post insulting and stupid.<br><br>
CLassLass has her own battles and demons to deal with, and apparently she will get the better of them in time. I ran in too quick, to macho perhaps, to want to protect her (hell, she is the only one to say something nice about me after all-that's a joke), but I was wrong to make it a joke at anyones expense. And now I am definately having a reaction, of deep sorrow and regret.<br><br>
Art, you will call it a flip flop, and I don't care. I just know that I am deeply moved by reading the posts above, and not ashamed to admit when I have been the wrong end of the horse. Cook, I personally apologize to you, I blew it by coming over to your side of the lake and breaking wind upwind from you. Crude and rude, and totally my stupidity. Sorry. I will attack or duel with you when it is of meaning and issues, and I am sorry to slander you over my trip.<br><br>
I'm so glad to see ClassLass back, and so pained to hear of her pain, I guess I needed to unleash. I had just come home from a 3 day, 14 hours a day, no breaks mediation between two parties, one being me, so I was just a wee bit stressed out. Driving 2 hours into Encino in rush hours didn't help either, or the chili burger off the dashboard on the way home, in the dark.  Not wise for a dress shirt and tie. Another joke I guess.<br><br>
No excuse. I should never have posted.  I will try and learn to unplug the modem and just play solitaire or Doom when I am too stressed out and waiting for the ETOH to hit. All I can do is say Opps, I seem to have stepped on it again. <br><br>
Doc Spatz
